commit.message:
strip leading space from ChangeLog

This makes it easier to copy & paste into GH release notes.
update for 0.4 version
update changelog for 0.3 release
set homepage in build tools
github: enable build+test CI action

fix undefined behavior with va_arg on 16-bit value

macOS produces this warning:
lzw.c:120:21: error:
    second argument to 'va_arg' is of promotable type 'mode_t' (aka 'unsigned short');
    this va_arg has undefined behavior because arguments will be promoted to 'int' [-Werror,-Wvarargs]
        mode = va_arg(ap, mode_t);
                          ^~~~~~
rework -Werror handling into a dedicated configure option
cleanup code comments

drop custom big endian unpacking

We can just let the compiler take care of this for us.

liblzw-config: drop old config script

pkg-config should be pretty ubiquitous at this point.

refresh build tools

Force automake-1.15 in the process.  Anyone generating autotools
should have a release from 6+ years ago.

Fix error when autotools cannot find README file

Make project 'foreign' since it not conform to GNU standards.

migrate to github

Signed-off-by: Mike Frysinger <vapier@gmail.com>

change copyright messages to purely author notices

Adding Copyright notices with public domain code doesn't make sense.

Signed-off-by: Mike Frysinger <vapier@gmail.com>

refresh build tools

Get it working nicely with latest autotools (automake-1.14 and
autoconf-2.69).
